A vintage-style illustration of an enormous, weathered filing cabinet stretching impossibly tall into a dusky amber sky, with countless drawers partially open at various angles. From the drawers, translucent threads and ribbons in muted gold and copper tones spill out and interweave, forming an intricate web that connects to smaller filing cabinets scattered across a misty landscape. Some threads fade into ghostly wisps while others remain vibrant and taut. Abandoned office chairs sit empty near some cabinets, their occupants long gone but their connections persisting. The scene has a melancholic, sepia-toned quality reminiscent of 1940s editorial illustrations, with soft crosshatching and aged paper texture throughout.
